{
  "stem": "11274.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, and then my mother decided that he-- I'm sitting a lot of time while he was busy with the boys.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a lot longer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and I'm not-- the boys are, are studying and practicing right there in the Temple.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Do you know any other language, she asked him, to teach my daughter?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he says yes, I know German.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he taught me German and Hebrew at the same time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And while I was going to school, to the Polish school, the Polish public school decided so long as we have Ruthenians in town, the, the children, all the Polish and Jewish children should know the language, too, and alphabet.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So in first grade we started with the alphabet, Polish and Ruthenian.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had Hebrew and German, [LAUGHS] at seven years, four languages, and Jewish at home.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So it's four languages, and the fifth one was at home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the other languages I learned later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I don't know if you know about Hasidic Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everything is observed like the-- on the Sabbath not to do anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, you fed the animals because that was necessary if you had a farm, like we did.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But no cooking.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we had a big oven at the, at the shochet's-- at the rabbi's home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, and you brought a cholent you made.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You made it on Friday, and you brought it in the afternoon, late, to the, to the home there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And his daughter [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Golda ?] was waiting for us and put it all in the oven.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were already prepared the oven with the coals went through it, and then the coals spread apart.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And by the next-- by Sabbat morning, they went all to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
